    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#CIG"/> <citedRange>5154</citedRange> (Franz)</bibl>, from 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#pacho1827"/>, pl. <citedRange>65, 9</citedRange></bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#smith-porcher1864"/>, n. <citedRange>27</citedRange></bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#mohamed-jmr1997"/>, pp. 34-35 n. <citedRange>4 C</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>47.2180, C</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>086400</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf.<bibl><ptr target="#cervelli1825"/>, p. <citedRange>26</citedRange> and pl. <citedRange>I.5 (erroneously numbered 3)</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#dthorn-thorn2009"/>, p. <citedRange>267</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2013"/>, p. <citedRange>185</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>64.2015</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/>, p. <citedRange>108</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63182"><name nymRef="#Ἀριστοτέλης">Ἀριστοτέλης</name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65720"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Σῶσις">Σώσιος</name></persName></persName> <rs type="office" key="eponymous priest"><w lemma="ἱαρεύς">ἱαρεὺς</w></rs>
                    <lb n="3"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Apollo"><name nymRef="#Ἀπόλλων">Ἀπόλλωνος</name></persName>· <w lemma="μηθείς">μηθέ<lb n="4" break="no"/>να</w> <w lemma="ἐντίθημι">ἐντίθη</w> <space quantity="5" unit="character" precision="low"/>.
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Aristoteles fils de Sosis, prêtre d'Apollon. N'enterrer personne d'autre.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Aristoteles son of Sosis, priest of Apollo. Don't bury anyone else here.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Before being copied by Pacho and from him edited in <bibl><ptr target="#CIG"/> <citedRange>5154</citedRange></bibl>, the inscription had been copied by Cervelli, who described the tomb in a few lines.</p>
                <p>From the same tomb, not precisely identified in the South Necropolis, comes <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr008100</ref> and might also come <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr086200</ref> and <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr086500</ref>.</p>
	     <p>An Aristoteles son of Sosis is mentioned among the contributors of <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr065200</ref>, about 280 BC. The lettering here indicates a date about the end of 
	         the second century. So a family link is possible, but cannot be fixed more precisely. <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/></bibl> considers that this Aristoteles would plausibly be the great-great-grandson 
	         of the contributor and dates his priesthood between 140 and 100 BC.</p>
	
            </div></body>
    </text>
